"v.使洁净，净化 【英】 v. 使洁净，净化( make pure) 【考】 purify : imperfection / verify : doubtfulness(净化排除缺点/证实 排除怀疑)winnow : grain / purify : water(扬谷把粮食中的杂质 去掉/净化把水中的杂 质去掉)反义词：contaminate (污染) 【记】 pur（纯洁）+ify（化 ）→纯洁化 v. 使纯洁(除去玷污物); 净化(灵魂) 【记】pur源于pure纯化 【类】purify: imperfection = verify: doubtfulness净化排除缺点 = 证实排除怀疑winnow: grain = purify: water扬谷把粮食中杂质去掉 = 净化把水中杂质去掉 【反】contaminate(v 污染) 【记】pure + fy使 purify (v.)  early 14c., ""free from spiritual pollution,"" from Old French purefier ""purify, cleanse, refine"" (12c.), from Latin purificare ""to make pure,"" from purus ""pure"" (see pure) + root of facere ""to make"" (see factitious). Meaning ""free from extraneous matter"" is recorded from mid-15c. Related: Purified; purifying."
